00099 /* Maximum value for windowBits in deflateInit2 and inflateInit2 */
00100 #ifndef MAX_WBITS
00101 #  define MAX_WBITS   15        /* 32K LZ77 window */
00102 #endif
00103 
00104 /* The memory requirements for deflate are (in bytes):
00105             1 << (windowBits+2)   +  1 << (memLevel+9)
00106  that is: 128K for windowBits=15  +  128K for memLevel = 8  (default values)
00107  plus a few kilobytes for small objects. For example, if you want to reduce
00108  the default memory requirements from 256K to 128K, compile with
00109      make CFLAGS="-O -DMAX_WBITS=14 -DMAX_MEM_LEVEL=7"
00110  Of course this will generally degrade compression (there's no free lunch).
00111 
00112    The memory requirements for inflate are (in bytes) 1 << windowBits
00113  that is, 32K for windowBits=15 (default value) plus a few kilobytes
00114  for small objects.
00115 */
00116
